  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved cookstoves prevent deforestation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Empower people to make their own improved cookstove using only locally available materials 2. Teach bio-charcoal production from renewable sources 3. A commitment to plant trees to counteract deforestation. This is the core of our hands-on comprehensive community workshop approach. Our research shows: our model of improved cookstoves reduce the need for fuel up to 75%. Our goal: Every household in our villages (and beyond) uses improved cookstoves, ideally with locally made bio-charcoal.</narrative>
  </description>
